@junrushao1994 during arguing, we already typed more words than the code...
I knew you want something like this
```
atomic<bool> b;
if(!b.load(acquire))
{
lock()
if(!b.load(acquire))
 initialize;
 b.store(true, release);
}
unlock();
}
```
But I personally don't like mix mutex with atomic, or too many atomic ops.
Maybe the following can satisfy my personal preference, and also address your concern for some weak ordering arch.
Note multi-calls in initialization are allowed. 
```
std::atomic_flag a;
volatile b;
if(!b)
{
while(a.test_and_set(rel_acq));
if(!b)
 initialize;
a.clear(release);
if(!b)
 b = true;
}
```
Or just feel free to change it by yourself. :)
